# 1. 未だ知らぬ伝説

Student: Class is adjourned!
Students: Finally... Time for lunch.
Students: I'm starving. Let's eat together!
Kohane: Phew... Lunchtime, lunchtime...
Minori: Kohane! Let's have lunch together♪
Kohane: Hi, Minori! Sure! Huh...?
Kohane: Shiho? You're not with Ichika and the others today?
Shiho: No, they're all busy with committee stuff today.
Kohane: Oh, okay. That's actually sort of nice since it's been a little while since we last had lunch together.
Minori: I know, right? We can have a special classroom lunch today!
Shiho: As in just having lunch in class?
Minori: It's special because you're here, Shiho! Let's put our desks together and...
Minori: Let's eat!
Kohane & Shiho: Let's eat.
Kohane: Oh, Shiho, your Salisbury steaks look so yummy.
Minori: She's right! Are these homemade, not frozen...?!
Shiho: Uh... Yeah... My mom makes these pretty often.
Shiho: She apparently wants to make sure I have plenty to eat since I'm always busy with the band and stuff.
Kohane: Hehe. Your mom sounds like such a nice person.
Shiho: Yeah, she really is.
Shiho: By the way, how's practice been going for you two lately?
Minori: Huh? Lately?
Shiho: Yeah. I'm kinda curious as to what kind of stuff you guys all practice.
Shiho: Take the Fan Festival for example. Remember how you met up with Kohane's group to practice singing, Minori?
Shiho: Ichika even talked about how that practice really opened her eyes.
Shiho: So I'm wondering if there are any good drills or tips you could tell me about.
Minori: Good drills...? Hmm... Do you have any ideas?
Kohane: Oh, maybe...
Kohane: My team is usually at its best when we have the same image or ideas in mind.
Minori: The same image?
Kohane: Yeah. We started working on this song and began wondering how we could capture the “serenity of a forest” so to speak.
Kohane: And it turned out that one of our teammates had never been to an actual forest before, which sort of kept us from syncing right.
Kohane: So we decided to go camping in a forest to fix that. As a result, we were able to sing this song really well because we all had the same image in our heads.
Shiho: I see... That is a pretty good idea.
Shiho: We watched a DVD of this famous band's concert together the other day and it really helped us get in sync.
Shiho: That must've also been because it gave us such a clear picture of what we needed to do.
Minori: Yeah, we usually work on dances while watching footage for a show as a reference and it always helps us get in sync!
Kohane: Is that true...?!
Minori: Hehe. It's like we all arrived at the same solution. Talk about a coincidence.
Shiho: It probably means having a clear picture of what you want to do or become is just that important.
Minori: What I want to become...? That's easy! A great idol, just like Haruka!
Shiho: That's just you, Minori. I was talking about what each of our groups are striving to become.
Minori: Oh, right! Hehe...
Kohane: Hehe.
Minori: Oh, that reminds me. You guys are trying to surpass that one event... RAD WEEKEND, right?
Minori: Does that mean you watch videos of that event as a team?
Kohane: Oh...
Kohane: Um... There aren't any videos out there.
Shiho: Really?
Kohane: Yeah. I tried asking An and the others a while back...
An: Yeah... There aren't any as far as I know.
Kohane: Not even one?
Akito: Yeah. No cameras were allowed during RAD WEEKEND.
Kohane: I see... That's really unfortunate.
An: To be fair, there probably wouldn't be any videos left regardless.
Kohane: Wait, what do you mean?
Toya: Based on what Akito's told me... Nobody there would've been taking pictures or videos.
An: Yeah, the whole place was nuts. They were all probably too immersed or focused on the show to record anything.
Akito: Since everybody has smartphones now, there's usually some kind of evidence out there showing that an event like that happened.
Akito: But that's not the case for this one. It's part of why it's become such a legendary event.
Kohane: I see...
Kohane: (So there's no way for me to see what happened...)
Minori: What?! Is that really true?!
Shiho: That's really unfortunate.
Kohane: It is... But it also tells me that it was just that incredible.
Minori: But...! Not being able to see it just makes you want to see it more, right?!
Kohane: You're right...
Kohane: (I was really hoping to see what An and Shinonome experienced, but I guess there really isn't anything I can do about it...)
Kohane: (But...)
